result.execSummary:
The defendant Cody P. Frame was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operate with Restricted Controlled Substance (Consolidated from Pepin Co Case 13CT09/14CF36), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(am).
  • OWI (6th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Staying Jail Time
IT IS ORDERED the defendant's remaining jail time is hereby ordered stayed as of January 7, 2015. The jail time will remain stayed pending good standing status in the Treatment Court and will be waived in the event the defendant continues with successful completion of the Eau Claire County Treatment Court Program requirements. The stayed jail time may be re-imposed for good cause.
